    <div class="sections">
        <div class="inner-header">
            <h2>A Customizable UI Framework for Full Nodes</h2>
            <p>Built in React, Redux, and Node, bPanel is an extensible UI framework that lets users interact with their nodes, 
            test ideas, and build entire applications quickly on multiple networks simultaneously. bPanel is easily used as a 
            base for your next crypto project.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="section section--odd section--one">
            <div class="section__text">
                <h2>Multi-Party Wallet, Block Explorer</h2>
                <div class="text">
                    <p>Installing bPanel comes with a standard set of plugins that are styled with the bMenace theme, including a multi-party wallet & block explorer.</p>
                    <p>With Ledger hardware support, you can manage your keys offline while using bPanel to handle multi-sig signing & spending.</p>
                    <a class="section-link" href="/docs/intro_plugin.html">Learn More</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="section__image">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="section section--even section--two">
            <div class="section__text">
                <h2>Modern Technology</h2>
                <div class="text">
                    <p>bPanel is built from the ground up using modern web development technologies like NodeJS and ES6 JavaScript.</p>
                    <p>With a standalone app server that acts as a proxy to your bcoin node using http requests and web sockets, 
                    you can configure your bpanel to point to anywhere you want.</p>
                    <p>bcoin is a trusted fullnode implementation built specifically for production systems at scale. 
                    Anything bcoin can do, bPanel can do too!</p>

                    <a class="section-link" href="https://bcoin.io">Visit bcoin.io</a>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="section__image">
            </div>
        </div>
